					<msContents class="lccn.loc.gov/sh85070287" rend="visible">
						<summary>Portions of the Judeo-Arabic commentary on the books I-V of Maimonides' Mishneh Torah, in the form of questions and answers. </summary>
						<textLang mainLang="jrb-Hebr" otherLangs="he"/>
						<msItem rend="visible" class="lccn.loc.gov/sh85070287">
							<locus from="1r" to="120v"/>
							<title xml:lang="en">Perush Mishneh Torah</title>
							<title xml:lang="he">פירוש משנה תורה</title>
							<author key="http://viaf.org/viaf/100185495">
								<persName key="http://viaf.org/viaf/100185495" xml:lang="en">Maimonides, Moses, 1135-1204</persName>
								<persName key="http://viaf.org/viaf/100185495" xml:lang="he">משה בן מימון, 1138-1204 </persName>
							</author>
							<note>
								<p>A large fragment of the same, or similar, commentary on the other books of the Mishneh Torah is contained in folios 175v-228r of Or 2746, probably compiled by Mosheh ben Yosef Albelidah.</p>
							</note>
						</msItem>
					</msContents>
					<physDesc rend="visible">
						<p>Paper codex of the 15th century.</p>
						<objectDesc form="codex">
							<supportDesc material="chart">
								<extent>120 folios <dimensions unit="mm" type="leaf">
										<height>250</height>
										<width>190</width>
									</dimensions>
									<dimensions type="written" unit="mm">
										<height>200</height>
										<width>130</width>
									</dimensions>
								</extent>
								<foliation>
									<p>120 folios (+ 2 unfoliated modern paper flyleaves at the beginning and at the end).</p>
								</foliation>
								<collation>
									<p>Quires of 10 leaves each, signed with Hebrew letters at the end, and also marked with catchwords. </p>
									<p>Only the quires no. 3-5, 7-8, and 10 are complete.</p>
								</collation>
								<condition>
									<p>Lacunae after folios 2, 54, 80, 96, 101, 106, 114. Missing portions at the beginning and at the end.</p>
									<p>Only a part of folio 57 is preserved.</p>
									<p>Several leaves damaged.</p>
								</condition>
							</supportDesc>
							<layoutDesc>
								<layout columns="1 " ruledLines="26" writtenLines="26">
									<p>Uniform layout. Ruled with mastara.</p>
									<p>Some marginal notes.</p>
									<p>Chapter titles and chapter numbers given in larger characters.</p>
								</layout>
							</layoutDesc>
